Bring a #large saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp} for the
@rigatoni pasta{180%g}.

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a #large frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once the oil is hot, add the @diced British chicken breast{260%g} and season with
@salt{} and @ground black pepper{}.

Cook until browned all over, ~{5-6%minutes}. IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and
equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Once browned, stir in the garlic, @Cajun spice mix{1}(add less if you'd prefer
things milder) and @tomato puree{30%g}. Cook for ~{1%minute} more.

Stir the @chopped tomatoes with onion and garlic{1%tin}, @chicken stock paste{10%g}
and @water{100%ml} for the sauce into the #pan.

Bring to the boil, stir and lower the heat so the sauce simmers gently.

Cook until the chicken is cooked through and the sauce has thickened,
~{10-12%minutes}. IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the
middle.

While the sauce simmers, add the rigatoni to your pan of boiling water. Cook
until tender, ~{12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back in the pan. Drizzle with oil
and stir through to stop it sticking together.

Meanwhile, preheat your #grill{} to high.

Once the sauce has thickened, stir in the @baby spinach{40%g}(washed) a handful
at a time until wilted and piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Combine the cooked pasta and sauce in whichever pan is biggest, then season
to taste with salt and pepper.

Transfer your Cajun pasta to an #ovenproof dish{} and sprinkle on the
@hard Italian style cheese{20%g}(grated).

Grill your pasta until the cheese is golden and bubbly, ~{2-3%minutes}.

When ready, share between your bowls and tuck in. Enjoy!